A former Military Administrator of Lagos State, Prince Olagunsoye Oyinlola, has described the death of the first military governor of Lagos State, General Mobolaji Johnson, as a great loss to Nigeria and the end of an era. Prince Oyinlola, in a statement issued on Thursday, said the late General lived a life without stain despite being a big player in government and in the corporate world. Nasarawa gov directs school principals to stop charging fees Ganduje wants death penalty for kidnappers in Kano State #CashAndcarryPrison: Aregbesola lauds Fisayo Soyombo,… Borno re-introduces monthly sanitation after 26 years ALSO READ: Mobolaji Johnson incorruptible, laid foundation of modern Lagos, says Agbaje He recalled all the moral and political support the late Johnson gave him when he administered Lagos between 1993 and 1996, describing the deceased as a father-figure to him even after he left Lagos. Prince Oyinlola, who was also a former governor of Osun State, while commiserating with the family of the deceased, the government and people of Lagos State, the military and the Federal Government, prayed God to grant his soul eternal peace. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
